<div class="header mb-4">
	<h2>The Beginning of the American Nation</h2>
</div>

<div class="content mb-4">
	<div>
		<p>Prepare yourself for a trip through time in Virginia’s Historic Triangle in Williamsburg, Jamestown, and Yorktown! Here, you can learn about history, ride exhilarating roller coasters, and dine on recipes that are both modern and centuries-old. The Williamsburg area is a perfect family getaway. It combines fun and learning into one trip.</p>
		<h3>Jamestown</h3>
		<p>Step back through the centuries to Jamestown. It was the first permanent English settlement on the North American continent. In the early 1600s, Captain John Smith, Pocahontas, and many others walked the shores of the James River. At Historic Jamestowne, explore the ruins of the English settlers’ church. Archaeologists are still unearthing artifacts from their lives. Nearby, at the Jamestown Settlement, costumed interpreters display how the English settlers lived and provided for themselves. You’ll also see a replica Powhatan Indian Village and re-creations of the ships that brought the English to Virginia.</p>
		<h3>Williamsburg</h3>
		<p>Journey along the Colonial Parkway to continue your historic adventure in Williamsburg. At Colonial Williamsburg, figures from the past including George Wythe, Patrick Henry, and Thomas Jefferson come to life through interpreters. Witness our calls for freedom and see the democracy that shaped our nation as though it was happening for the first time. Step into the restored and reconstructed homes, shops, government buildings and taverns from the past. </p>
		<h3>Yorktown</h3>
		<p>Yorktown is where the patriots’ fight for independence was won. Walk the battlefield to see the fields where the Redcoats and the Patriots clashed. Then, explore the American Revolution Museum at Yorktown to find out more about the heroes and stories from the war for independence.</p>
	</div>
</div>